  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Better WASH for Healthy Nepal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The quality of water supply in Nepal is always questionable due to lack of proper treatment system, pollution at source, no use of disinfection and no proper maintenance of water distribution system. Sanitation-related diseases account for 72% of total ailments and diarrhea continues to be one of the leading causes of childhood deaths in Nepal. COVID-19 outbreak has also created unprecedented health crisis. There is also indoor air pollution due to the use of traditional firewood cookstove.</narrative>
  </description>
